WEBVTT

00:02.470 --> 00:05.537
[lock jiggling]

00:05.539 --> 00:07.906
Adult mark:<i> The old man</i>
<i> slept like a baby.</i>

00:08.042 --> 00:09.875
<i> A teething baby.</i>

00:10.010 --> 00:11.143
[quietly]
locked.

00:11.145 --> 00:12.710
Unlocked.

00:12.747 --> 00:14.379
Locked.
Unlocked.

00:14.382 --> 00:15.914
Adult mark:<i> Dad couldn't sleep</i>
<i> until he double-checked,</i>

00:15.916 --> 00:18.049
<i> Triple-checked, and</i>
<i> quadruple-checked the locks.</i>

00:18.051 --> 00:19.184
Mike sr: Off.

00:19.253 --> 00:20.719
Off.

00:20.854 --> 00:22.788
Adult mark:<i> And checked</i>
<i> and blessed every burner.</i>

00:22.857 --> 00:24.990
...The father, son,
and holy ghost...

00:25.125 --> 00:27.659
Mary: Will you quit packin'
around and come to bed?

00:27.661 --> 00:29.994
Pop: Shut up!
I'm trying to sleep!

00:30.031 --> 00:32.264
Shut up yourself, you old coot!

00:32.399 --> 00:34.600
Adult mark:<i> Everything in</i>
<i> the house had to be unplugged.</i>

00:34.602 --> 00:36.268
Father, son, and the holy ghost.
Off!

00:36.337 --> 00:38.537
Adult mark:<i> Dad worked on</i>
<i> american bases during the war,</i>

00:38.606 --> 00:40.406
<i> And the army safety films</i>
<i> had burned themselves</i>

00:40.541 --> 00:42.774
<i> Into his brain.</i>

00:42.843 --> 00:45.544
Announcer: Plug in that
christmas tree, and whammo!

00:45.546 --> 00:49.615
This gi's christmas
has gone up in smoke!

00:49.617 --> 00:50.749
[door slams]
[mary gasps]

00:50.884 --> 00:52.150
Pop: For crying out loud!

00:52.186 --> 00:54.752
Mike jr: Sorry, sorry!

00:54.789 --> 00:57.956
Better make sure
that door's locked.

00:57.958 --> 01:00.425
Oh, for frig's sake!

01:00.428 --> 01:02.927
Mike sr: Locked...
Unlocked...

01:02.963 --> 01:05.464
Locked...
Unlocked...

01:05.599 --> 01:08.733
Locked...
Unlocked...

01:08.803 --> 01:11.002
Mary: Mike, honey,
get your arse in gear.

01:11.038 --> 01:12.571
The cab'll be here soon!

01:12.573 --> 01:14.706
Adult mark:<i> Normally</i>
<i> there was no privacy at all</i>

01:14.742 --> 01:17.776
<i>In our little house, but this</i>
<i> night was a perfect storm.</i>

01:17.778 --> 01:19.445
<i> My brother was working</i>
<i> the night shift</i>

01:19.580 --> 01:20.512
<i> At the radio station,</i>

01:20.647 --> 01:22.648
<i> Pop would be asleep by 7,</i>

01:22.783 --> 01:25.717
<i>And my folks were celebrating</i>
<i> their 20th anniversary</i>

01:25.753 --> 01:27.219
<i> By going somewhere</i>
<i> they'd never been...</i>

01:27.354 --> 01:28.520
<i> Out!</i>

01:28.589 --> 01:30.589
Mike sr: I don't know, mary.
Freezing rain.

01:30.591 --> 01:31.857
It's gettin' pretty greasy out.

01:31.992 --> 01:33.992
Well, that's why
we're taking a cab!

01:33.994 --> 01:36.528
That and I plan on
having two fuzzy navels.

01:36.663 --> 01:38.330
Oh, a night out!

01:38.332 --> 01:39.797
I don't care
if it's spitting lava.

01:39.834 --> 01:41.867
I'm having fun!

01:42.002 --> 01:43.535
Mark!

01:43.604 --> 01:45.537
You and ritche enjoy your movie
and behave yourselves.

01:45.672 --> 01:46.872
Mark: Sure, mom.

01:47.007 --> 01:49.274
Can't wait.

01:49.343 --> 01:53.879
Adult mark:<i> We pooled</i>
<i> our money to rent a vcr!</i>

01:53.948 --> 01:57.482
<i> With no one watching us,</i>
<i> we could watch what we wanted.</i>

01:57.485 --> 01:58.817
<i> Porky's.</i>

01:58.819 --> 02:01.286
<i> The citizen kane</i>
<i> of teen sex comedies.</i>

02:01.322 --> 02:03.421
<i> Ritche "borrowed"</i>
<i> his dad's copy.</i>

02:03.457 --> 02:07.493
♪

02:07.628 --> 02:11.563
♪

02:11.698 --> 02:13.265
♪

02:13.400 --> 02:15.334
Uh, I don't know, ritche.

02:15.336 --> 02:16.501
It's rated r.

02:16.537 --> 02:18.236
That means we need
parental guidance.

02:18.305 --> 02:20.639
This thing is
supposed to be filthy!

02:20.708 --> 02:22.741
You want to see boobies
with your parents at home?

02:22.876 --> 02:24.276
Adult mark:<i> I was</i>
<i> getting cold feet,</i>

02:24.411 --> 02:25.777
<i> But ritche was boiling over.</i>

02:25.913 --> 02:28.380
Gross!
No!

02:28.515 --> 02:29.915
This is supposed
to be the biggest film

02:29.984 --> 02:31.649
In canadian history.

02:31.685 --> 02:34.052
I'm strictly interested
in the comedic elements.

02:34.121 --> 02:35.254
It's research.

02:35.389 --> 02:37.455
Sure.
Okay.

02:37.525 --> 02:39.791
You close your eyes
when there's boobies, then.

02:39.793 --> 02:41.793
Let's not get carried away.

02:41.795 --> 02:45.130
♪

02:45.199 --> 02:48.033
♪

02:51.906 --> 02:54.406
Hell of a bad night.

02:54.408 --> 02:55.807
Hey, look at
the wires on that thing!

02:55.943 --> 02:57.542
My god, you're
gonna blow a fuse!

02:57.578 --> 02:59.344
News anchor: A storm warning
tonight across the province,

02:59.413 --> 03:00.879
As extreme weather
is expected to continue.

03:01.014 --> 03:02.414
Power lines are already...

03:02.549 --> 03:04.883
Mike sr: This could be the worst
ice storm we've ever seen.

03:04.885 --> 03:07.352
Pop: Pssht, I've seen worse
storms in a snow globe!

03:07.354 --> 03:09.087
News anchor: [on tv]
high winds, black ice,

03:09.156 --> 03:11.122
Freezing rain,
and poor visibility.

03:11.158 --> 03:14.325
The rnc are encouraging drivers
to stay where you're to.

03:14.361 --> 03:16.094
Mary...

03:16.096 --> 03:17.496
I think we should
stay home out of it.

03:17.631 --> 03:19.130
This is a death trap.

03:19.166 --> 03:21.700
I'm not staying here
on our 20th anniversary!

03:21.769 --> 03:24.335
People on death row
gets out more than I do!

03:24.371 --> 03:26.037
Uh, she has a point, dad.

03:26.106 --> 03:27.439
It's ponderosa!

03:27.441 --> 03:29.574
Twenty years of marriage
is a long time,

03:29.576 --> 03:31.510
But I hear
the salad bar is endless!

03:31.512 --> 03:34.179
What's a little freezin' rain?

03:34.248 --> 03:37.115
Pop: The boy's right, you know?
This is nothing.

03:37.117 --> 03:40.652
I mean, when I was his age,
we didn't even have electricity.

03:40.787 --> 03:43.721
I had to use an outhouse!

03:43.757 --> 03:46.524
Oh no, once it was so cold,

03:46.594 --> 03:49.527
I went out to have a pee
and it froze.

03:49.597 --> 03:52.163
I had to break it off midstream!

03:52.199 --> 03:54.866
Dick: [on radio] kiwanis club
bingo night is cancelled.

03:54.868 --> 03:57.536
The bonavista Sunday
stitch & bitch is cancelled.

03:57.671 --> 03:58.870
It's bad out there, folks!

03:58.939 --> 04:01.139
Since when do you
listen to dick dunphy?

04:01.141 --> 04:02.874
I think it's clearing up.

04:02.876 --> 04:04.342
Mike sr: Mary...

04:04.378 --> 04:07.012
I just saw the light and power
boys go up the road.

04:07.147 --> 04:09.181
They'll have the lights back on
by the time we gets there.

04:09.316 --> 04:10.282
Mary...

04:10.284 --> 04:11.750
I know.

04:11.819 --> 04:15.253
I'm never gonna see the inside
of that packin' ponderosa.

04:15.256 --> 04:18.022
Adult mark:<i> And I'd never see</i>
<i>the outside of kim cattrall.</i>

04:18.058 --> 04:19.358
<i> They couldn't stay!</i>

04:19.493 --> 04:21.693
Did you give up
on 20 years of marriage

04:21.729 --> 04:23.428
When things got tough?

04:23.430 --> 04:26.231
Queen-size-cut
prime rib dinner

04:26.233 --> 04:29.167
With all-you-can-eat salad bar
and baked potato,

04:29.236 --> 04:31.036
All for $5.39?

04:31.105 --> 04:32.838
The only ice you
should be worrying about

04:32.973 --> 04:35.040
Is the ice
in your dr. Peppers!

04:35.175 --> 04:36.441
Ritche: Yeah!

04:36.443 --> 04:37.909
Dick: [on radio]
the avalon mall is closed.

04:38.045 --> 04:39.377
Jade gardens is closed.

04:39.513 --> 04:41.747
And the ponderosa has closed.

04:41.749 --> 04:42.714
The magic wok has closed...

04:42.750 --> 04:44.416
Aw, frig.

04:44.418 --> 04:47.319
I'm just really sorry for you.

04:47.454 --> 04:50.989
[radio static]

04:51.124 --> 04:52.457
Good god!

04:52.459 --> 04:53.992
Dead air!

04:54.127 --> 04:55.860
I gotta get up to
the station, mary.

04:55.929 --> 04:58.230
They're gonna need all hands
on deck for this one.

04:58.365 --> 05:00.599
Happy friggin' anniversary.

05:00.734 --> 05:02.967
Adult mark:<i> In newfoundland,</i>
<i> we put salt on everything.</i>

05:03.037 --> 05:06.338
<i> Fish, potatoes...</i>

05:06.340 --> 05:07.539
Mike sr: Augh!

05:07.674 --> 05:08.740
Adult mark:<i> And the steps.</i>

05:08.776 --> 05:11.743
Mike sr: Mary!
You didn't salt!

05:11.878 --> 05:13.278
Mike!

05:13.280 --> 05:14.546
Mike sr: Ah, I packed my back!

05:14.681 --> 05:18.116
Abort mission!
Unplug the vcr!

05:18.185 --> 05:20.418
Um, is it the red wire
or the white wire?

05:20.487 --> 05:21.753
No time!
Just pull them all!

05:21.888 --> 05:23.355
Just all of them!

05:23.490 --> 05:24.556
Okay.

05:24.625 --> 05:26.691
Mike sr: Aah, my back!

05:26.694 --> 05:29.895
Oh god, my back!

05:30.030 --> 05:31.496
Pop: Watch out.
Mike sr: Augh!

05:31.498 --> 05:33.097
Mark: Are you okay, dad?

05:33.099 --> 05:34.366
Pop: Alright, nice and easy.

05:34.368 --> 05:35.367
Easy, easy.

05:35.502 --> 05:37.769
Augh, god!

05:37.838 --> 05:39.237
Augh!

05:39.239 --> 05:42.040
Even your back
goes out more than I do.

05:42.175 --> 05:46.645
Look, if you're not going
to the ponderosa, then...

05:46.647 --> 05:48.312
What are we gonna do for supper?

05:48.349 --> 05:49.715
Oh, jeez.

05:49.850 --> 05:54.252
[phone rings]

05:54.321 --> 05:56.587
Hello?
It's young mike.

05:56.589 --> 05:57.989
The station!
Give it, give it, give it!

05:58.025 --> 06:01.259
Come on, will ya?

06:01.328 --> 06:02.827
Hello?

06:02.863 --> 06:04.862
The weight of the ice
toppled the power line, mike.

06:04.898 --> 06:06.264
She's gone.

06:06.333 --> 06:08.333
Mike sr: Yeah, so's my back.
I can't come up.

06:08.402 --> 06:09.868
So, what do we do?

06:09.870 --> 06:11.269
Mike sr: Alright,
listen carefully, dick!

06:11.405 --> 06:12.938
You gotta go out to
the generator, alright?

06:13.073 --> 06:14.406
There's a big yellow box.

06:14.541 --> 06:16.541
Pull the lever inside
and the generator will kick in.

06:16.543 --> 06:18.443
Right on, mike.
Thanks, dad.

06:18.578 --> 06:21.279
I can get the generator going,
but she's old.

06:21.281 --> 06:23.414
I'll have to stay up there
and keep an eye on her.

06:23.450 --> 06:25.684
You'll have to go
on the air by yourself

06:25.686 --> 06:28.219
Till the road's clear enough
to get someone else in.

06:28.255 --> 06:30.822
But that could be all night!

06:30.957 --> 06:33.725
You got the gift of the gab
from your old man...

06:33.727 --> 06:36.027
And your mudder.

06:36.162 --> 06:39.631
♪

06:39.633 --> 06:43.568
[rain pouring]

06:43.637 --> 06:46.371
After 20 friggin' years you'd
think I'd get one night off

06:46.506 --> 06:47.906
For good behaviour.

06:47.975 --> 06:50.842
Mike sr: [groans]

06:50.878 --> 06:53.244
I guess we could watch
the movie that the boys got.

06:53.313 --> 06:54.579
No!

06:54.581 --> 06:55.913
Oh.

06:55.949 --> 06:57.582
Aw, porky's.

06:57.584 --> 07:00.218
The little pig
with the stutter, sin.

07:00.254 --> 07:01.986
I could use a laugh.

07:02.055 --> 07:03.455
How do you turn it on?

07:03.457 --> 07:06.858
Uh, actually it won't work.

07:06.894 --> 07:07.993
'cause of the storm, you know?

07:08.128 --> 07:09.527
Yeah.

07:09.596 --> 07:12.664
Oh, the doohickeys are out.

07:12.666 --> 07:14.466
There.

07:14.601 --> 07:16.201
Hm!
See?

07:16.270 --> 07:20.071
When did you start
work at radio shack?

07:20.107 --> 07:24.075
The fbi?
Is this even legal?

07:24.144 --> 07:25.811
Adult mark:<i> I never</i>
<i> needed therapy</i>

07:25.946 --> 07:28.413
<i> Because I already know where</i>
<i> all my problems come from:</i>

07:28.548 --> 07:31.383
<i> Watching porky's</i>
<i> with my parents!</i>

07:33.487 --> 07:35.786
Oh...

07:36.890 --> 07:38.290
What did I miss?

07:38.292 --> 07:39.757
Adult mark:<i> A black out...</i>

07:39.759 --> 07:42.093
<i> Right before I would have</i>
<i> blacked out!</i>

07:42.095 --> 07:44.095
The damned thing blew a fuse!

07:44.231 --> 07:46.430
I'll get it.

07:46.467 --> 07:48.766
Dah... Aaaugh!
My back!

07:54.808 --> 07:56.774
Adult mark:<i> I prayed</i>
<i> the lights never came back.</i>

07:56.810 --> 08:00.611
[phone ringing]

08:00.647 --> 08:02.113
Mark: Come on, open!
Open up!

08:02.115 --> 08:04.715
Hello?

08:04.751 --> 08:06.584
Oh...
It's alice.

08:06.720 --> 08:08.753
She says the power's out
all over the city.

08:08.755 --> 08:10.922
That damn thing blew
the power for the whole city?

08:10.924 --> 08:12.557
No!
It's because of the ice storm,

08:12.692 --> 08:14.959
You stunned arse!

08:15.094 --> 08:16.528
The tape's stuck inside!

08:16.597 --> 08:18.663
We need to get it out before
the lights come back on!

08:18.699 --> 08:21.666
We can't without power!

08:23.904 --> 08:25.604
No!

08:25.739 --> 08:27.272
You'll ruin my dad's tape!

08:27.407 --> 08:30.508
My dad will ruin us
if he sees a b-o-o-b!

08:32.679 --> 08:35.013
Okay, I have an idea.

08:35.148 --> 08:37.415
Get me a butter knife.

08:37.484 --> 08:38.383
Okay.

08:38.518 --> 08:39.951
Okay, go.

08:40.086 --> 08:42.954
It's gonna get cold,
so you better bundle up, hm?

08:43.023 --> 08:44.889
Okay.

08:44.891 --> 08:47.425
[chuckles]
come on, boys.

08:47.461 --> 08:49.561
This is nothing!

08:49.563 --> 08:52.830
You know, before he led
peary to the pole,

08:52.900 --> 08:55.901
Captain bob bartlett and I
used to take the dog sleds

08:56.036 --> 08:58.970
Way up north just to relax!

08:58.972 --> 09:00.305
Yeah.

09:00.307 --> 09:03.908
Of course when it got
really, really cold,

09:03.977 --> 09:06.644
The dogs died.

09:06.780 --> 09:09.581
Imagine being so desperate
for survival

09:09.716 --> 09:12.250
That you eat your best friend.

09:12.319 --> 09:15.787
First you lose your fingers...

09:15.856 --> 09:18.923
Then you lose your toes...

09:18.992 --> 09:23.728
Then finally... Your mind.

09:23.863 --> 09:27.732
[slurps loudly]

09:29.069 --> 09:30.335
Ooh...

09:30.404 --> 09:31.869
Pineapple crush?

09:31.939 --> 09:34.171
Hm?

09:39.012 --> 09:42.580
[whirring and buzzing]

09:48.021 --> 09:50.755
Uh, hello!

09:50.791 --> 09:53.491
This is mike critch.

09:53.527 --> 09:54.759
Not my dad, mike critch.

09:54.761 --> 09:56.094
He's not with us.

09:56.229 --> 09:58.697
The other mike critch, his son.

09:58.832 --> 10:00.064
Me.

10:00.100 --> 10:01.433
Um...

10:01.568 --> 10:04.835
Do you have power where you are?

10:04.871 --> 10:09.040
Call in and let me know.

10:15.115 --> 10:17.816
Mike sr: Come on...

10:17.951 --> 10:19.384
Old woman: [on radio]
it's so dark!

10:19.453 --> 10:21.453
I'm froze to death!
I can't--

10:21.588 --> 10:23.288
Vocm's back on!

10:23.290 --> 10:25.190
Mike jr: It'll all be
over soon, ma'am.

10:25.325 --> 10:27.058
I bet you've survived
worse than this.

10:27.193 --> 10:28.460
Where the hell is dick?

10:28.595 --> 10:30.795
It's a major news story,
he's got a child on the air!

10:30.797 --> 10:32.330
Old woman: I was
a little girl then...

10:32.332 --> 10:34.065
Mary: Aw!
Old woman: ...But I remembers!

10:34.101 --> 10:35.467
Mike jr: You know what they say

10:35.469 --> 10:37.001
About the weather
in newfoundland?

10:37.070 --> 10:39.804
If you don't like the weather,
just wait a minute!

10:39.806 --> 10:42.073
Oh, mike, our son's
on the radio!

10:42.208 --> 10:43.942
Good god, he should be
interviewing the mayor,

10:43.944 --> 10:45.543
Not some old bat!

10:45.612 --> 10:48.012
I gotta get over there.

10:48.015 --> 10:49.681
Mary: Ah, geez.

10:49.750 --> 10:53.284
Mike jr: My pop says, tea is
the remedy to anything, huh?

10:53.320 --> 10:55.720
Old woman: I'm scared
I'm gonna fall,

10:55.756 --> 10:58.089
And I'm all alone.

10:58.224 --> 10:59.290
Where you at, ma'am?

10:59.326 --> 11:01.559
Old woman: 31 gower street.

11:01.561 --> 11:04.228
Okay, if anyone's listening
around gower street,

11:04.264 --> 11:07.165
And you've got spare blankets
or a kerosene heater

11:07.167 --> 11:09.701
And you can get there,
we could really use your help.

11:09.836 --> 11:11.369
Old woman: Oh,
bless your heart!

11:11.438 --> 11:14.773
So sorry to hear your father
is no longer with us.

11:14.775 --> 11:17.742
Oh! No, no, no, he's just--
[phone hangs up]

11:17.778 --> 11:18.809
Mike jr: Mike critch junior...

11:18.845 --> 11:20.178
He's up there
making an arse of it.

11:20.313 --> 11:21.112
I gotta get up there.

11:21.247 --> 11:22.413
Absolutely not!

11:22.449 --> 11:23.414
Mike jr: The phone lines
are full right now--

11:23.483 --> 11:26.518
Mary!
[radio switches off]

11:26.520 --> 11:28.453
You boys are freezing.
Where are your blankets?

11:28.455 --> 11:31.055
Where is that kerosene heater?

11:31.058 --> 11:32.390
What are you doing?

11:32.392 --> 11:34.392
Uh, nothing!

11:34.527 --> 11:36.060
Just playing with knives!

11:36.129 --> 11:38.463
Adult mark:<i> Ritche wasn't</i>
<i> the sharpest knife in the vcr.</i>

11:38.532 --> 11:39.798
Uh...

11:39.800 --> 11:43.067
It's so rare to have
the family all together,

11:43.136 --> 11:44.803
With no tv to distract us.

11:44.805 --> 11:46.337
This is quality time.

11:46.472 --> 11:49.474
You know, we should be swapping
stories, trading tales,

11:49.476 --> 11:51.075
Getting to know
each other better!

11:51.078 --> 11:52.744
Well, sure, I know you,

11:52.813 --> 11:54.879
But do I know-know you?

11:54.881 --> 11:57.615
Well, for instance, dad,
what's your favourite colour?

11:57.684 --> 11:58.949
I dunno.

11:58.985 --> 12:00.017
Plaid.

12:00.053 --> 12:01.085
Ask your mudder.

12:01.154 --> 12:02.687
He's right.

12:02.689 --> 12:04.889
Why be alone
on our 20th anniversary

12:04.891 --> 12:06.758
When we can be with family?

12:06.760 --> 12:08.026
And ritche.

12:08.028 --> 12:09.494
[knife clanks down]

12:09.563 --> 12:12.130
Alright, what do you wanna know?

12:12.199 --> 12:15.333
Well... Is this the coldest
you've ever been?

12:15.335 --> 12:16.501
Good god, no.

12:16.570 --> 12:17.968
This is nothing
compared to greenland.

12:17.970 --> 12:19.703
Greenland?

12:19.740 --> 12:22.106
Oh, when were you in greenland?

12:22.109 --> 12:23.641
Oh, years ago.

12:23.677 --> 12:26.177
Before I met you.
With the yanks.

12:26.179 --> 12:27.645
You guys don't really
want to hear

12:27.714 --> 12:30.047
A bunch of old boring stories
from 30 years ago, do you?

12:30.049 --> 12:32.750
I do!

12:32.753 --> 12:35.920
Well, I worked on some
american bases after the war.

12:36.055 --> 12:38.456
Nothing special, just some...

12:38.525 --> 12:41.726
Office administration.

12:41.728 --> 12:43.994
I'm not supposed to say,
but what the hell.

12:44.030 --> 12:46.464
It was a long time ago now.

12:46.599 --> 12:48.900
In the 60's,
I worked at a secret base

12:49.035 --> 12:51.536
Under the polar ice cap
in greenland.

12:51.605 --> 12:53.671
Project ice worm,
they called it.

12:53.707 --> 12:55.739
We had 600 nukes stored there.

12:55.776 --> 12:58.275
You know,
in case of a war with russia.

12:58.277 --> 13:02.213
You don't know cold until you've
experienced cold war cold.

13:02.249 --> 13:05.749
Anyway, my point is,
it was freezing.

13:05.786 --> 13:08.753
You were basically
a henchman in a bond movie!

13:08.822 --> 13:10.421
Mike.

13:10.423 --> 13:13.091
Twenty years of marriage,
and you never told me that!

13:13.093 --> 13:14.258
Nukes!

13:14.294 --> 13:15.459
Cool!

13:15.495 --> 13:16.561
No.

13:16.630 --> 13:18.162
That's not the important part.

13:18.165 --> 13:22.500
The interesting thing is,
it was bitterly cold.

13:22.635 --> 13:25.837
Adult mark:<i> I thought I knew</i>
<i> everything about my father.</i>

13:25.906 --> 13:27.972
<i> But I realized</i>
<i> I didn't know much at all.</i>

13:27.974 --> 13:29.574
What else?

13:29.709 --> 13:31.442
You don't really want to hear
all this old stuff, do ya?

13:31.511 --> 13:33.845
All: Yes!
Please.

13:33.847 --> 13:35.747
[sighs]
alright.

13:35.882 --> 13:38.249
Mike sr: Well, there was
this one time, I got the call.

13:38.318 --> 13:39.684
Yes, sir.

13:39.686 --> 13:41.719
Mike sr: Red alert.

13:41.855 --> 13:44.255
A russian plane had
wandered into our airspace,

13:44.257 --> 13:46.658
And for the first time ever,
it was all systems go!

13:46.793 --> 13:48.726
Pop: Lord almighty!

13:48.862 --> 13:52.063
Oh, it's sweltering in here!

13:52.132 --> 13:54.732
I found these popsicles
in the freezer.

13:54.801 --> 13:56.600
You better eat 'em
before they melt,

13:56.636 --> 13:59.470
Which won't be long
in this heat!

13:59.506 --> 14:01.972
Mmm, mm-hm.

14:02.008 --> 14:03.708
Line 2, you're on the air!

14:03.843 --> 14:05.142
Man: The missus just
went into labour

14:05.212 --> 14:06.878
And the ambulance
can't get up the road!

14:07.013 --> 14:08.279
Where're you at, sir?

14:08.281 --> 14:10.348
Man: Downing street!
Mike jr: Okay!

14:10.350 --> 14:13.217
Uh, if you can get to
downing street, we need shovels!

14:13.286 --> 14:15.019
Woman: Honey, my contractions!

14:15.154 --> 14:18.857
[screams]

14:18.992 --> 14:20.458
Cold?

14:20.527 --> 14:22.093
[exhales]

14:22.162 --> 14:24.829
You can't even
see your breath in here.

14:24.898 --> 14:27.164
I mean, you crowd,
you're so soft.

14:27.166 --> 14:30.301
The great sealing disaster
of 1914.

14:30.337 --> 14:33.771
Now, that was cold.

14:33.840 --> 14:37.909
Men died hugging
each other for warmth.

14:37.978 --> 14:40.244
They froze like that.

14:40.313 --> 14:41.779
Should have seen them!

14:41.815 --> 14:46.183
Being lowered from the deck
of their ship like statues.

14:48.154 --> 14:52.256
[wind whistling eerily]

14:54.594 --> 14:57.929
Mark... If we die,

14:57.931 --> 14:59.830
You're not gonna let him
eat me, will you?

14:59.900 --> 15:01.065
Don't let him distract you!

15:01.200 --> 15:03.067
Think about porky's.
Stay warm that way.

15:03.202 --> 15:04.735
And get that tape out!

15:04.771 --> 15:07.538
Okay.

15:07.540 --> 15:10.875
[grunts]

15:10.877 --> 15:13.111
This isn't working!

15:13.113 --> 15:14.745
I think I need
something smaller.

15:14.781 --> 15:16.414
Oh.

15:16.416 --> 15:18.549
I know.
A popsicle stick!

15:18.551 --> 15:20.718
Popsicle stick...

15:20.754 --> 15:24.822
♪

15:24.891 --> 15:28.960
♪

15:28.962 --> 15:30.561
Pop, you took the heater!

15:30.563 --> 15:32.463
It's a million degrees
in here!

15:32.465 --> 15:34.098
Close the door, b'y!

15:34.233 --> 15:35.700
You're letting all the heat out!

15:38.438 --> 15:40.505
E chicken.

15:40.640 --> 15:44.976
Pop!
You're hogging all the heat!

15:45.111 --> 15:47.945
You know, bob barlett
made over 40 expeditions

15:47.981 --> 15:51.816
To the arctic,
and he died warm in his bed.

15:51.885 --> 15:53.818
Do you know how he did that?

15:53.820 --> 15:54.952
How?

15:54.988 --> 15:57.588
Pop: Because when
the crap hit the fan,

15:57.590 --> 16:01.258
He knew it was
every man for himself.

16:01.260 --> 16:04.996
Adult mark:<i> I was</i>
<i> too cold to argue.</i>

16:05.065 --> 16:09.000
♪

16:09.135 --> 16:12.536
Ritche: I can feel
my nose again!

16:12.672 --> 16:14.806
Mike jr: [on radio] dick dunphy,
if you can hear me...

16:14.808 --> 16:16.407
Mike sr: Aah!

16:16.542 --> 16:18.409
Mike jr: ...I could really use
a pee, so get back when you can.

16:18.544 --> 16:20.945
Mike critch jr., keeping you
company in the dark!

16:21.014 --> 16:22.747
Keep callin' in, folks.

16:22.749 --> 16:23.948
You're really
the only way I know

16:24.017 --> 16:25.149
If anyone out there
is listening!

16:25.284 --> 16:26.417
You look like a beached whale.

16:26.486 --> 16:27.618
I've gotta get to the station.

16:27.620 --> 16:29.219
It's devolved into chaos!

16:29.255 --> 16:31.155
Mike jr: [on radio] if anyone
spots a white tabby

16:31.157 --> 16:33.491
In the east end,
her name is kat with a k.

16:33.493 --> 16:35.225
Sounds like mike's
handling it just fine.

16:35.261 --> 16:37.895
But I gotta...

16:37.964 --> 16:40.631
You know, every year
on our anniversary,

16:40.700 --> 16:42.700
You have to work.

16:42.835 --> 16:46.571
And I say, "that's okay.
It's just our 18th."

16:46.706 --> 16:51.909
Or, "that's fine.
It's only our 19th."

16:51.978 --> 16:55.046
Well, now it's our
20th friggin' anniversary,

16:55.048 --> 16:57.115
And the only thing
that gets your attention

16:57.117 --> 17:00.584
Is that packin' radio!

17:00.620 --> 17:02.586
Mary?

17:02.655 --> 17:05.456
Mary!

17:05.458 --> 17:07.191
[grunts]

17:07.193 --> 17:08.726
Mike jr: [on radio]
okay, what else? Um...

17:08.795 --> 17:10.862
Oh, bell island ferries
are tied up for the night.

17:10.997 --> 17:12.797
Adult mark:<i> It took</i>
<i> a blackout to make dad</i>

17:12.799 --> 17:14.065
<i> Finally see the light.</i>

17:14.134 --> 17:16.534
[grunting]

17:16.536 --> 17:19.136
♪

17:21.241 --> 17:23.273
Next caller, you're on!

17:23.309 --> 17:26.077
Mayor: This is
the mayor calling.

17:26.079 --> 17:27.879
Mr. Mayor!
Hello, sir!

17:28.014 --> 17:29.547
Wha-- what can I do for you?

17:29.682 --> 17:32.283
Mayor: Firstly, I want to
thank you and everyone at vocm.

17:32.418 --> 17:34.752
You're the only station
still on the air.

17:34.887 --> 17:36.353
We are?

17:36.389 --> 17:38.122
Mayor: And condolences
on the loss of your father.

17:38.191 --> 17:39.457
Big shoes to fill.

17:39.526 --> 17:41.492
Oh, no, here's the thing.
He's not--

17:41.494 --> 17:43.094
[phone hangs up]

17:43.096 --> 17:45.496
And that was an exclusive
update from mayor murphy

17:45.532 --> 17:47.965
On the only station
still on the air.

17:48.001 --> 17:49.366
So I guess...

17:49.402 --> 17:51.035
We're number one!

17:51.104 --> 17:54.438
This is mike critch
for the vocm news service.

17:56.442 --> 17:57.608
Junior!

17:57.610 --> 17:59.810
Mike critch, junior.

17:59.846 --> 18:02.413
Pop?
Would you like a candle?

18:02.415 --> 18:03.881
You shaggers!

18:03.883 --> 18:07.184
Hey, don't tell mike
and come and join us.

18:07.253 --> 18:10.721
Pick it up.

18:10.723 --> 18:12.990
Mary: Boys, pick it up!
Mark: Mom!

18:13.059 --> 18:14.992
Mary: Move!
Mark: Okay, okay, okay.

18:15.128 --> 18:17.862
Never in my life
have I seen such selfish,

18:17.997 --> 18:21.465
Greedy buggers as you lot!

18:21.468 --> 18:23.601
What the frig
are you doing there?

18:23.736 --> 18:26.137
Happy 20th anniversary, mary.

18:26.272 --> 18:29.373
There's nobody
I'd rather be trapped with.

18:29.409 --> 18:34.345
Did you crawl
all that way to do this?

18:34.414 --> 18:36.947
Oh...

18:36.983 --> 18:39.683
♪

18:39.719 --> 18:41.285
Pop: Don't blow it out!

18:41.420 --> 18:43.220
Argh, it's freezing in here!

18:43.289 --> 18:44.688
Come here.

18:44.757 --> 18:47.892
Remember what
captain bob bartlett said:

18:48.027 --> 18:51.095
It's important to
share bodily heat.

18:51.097 --> 18:54.064
Didn't he say it
was every man for himself?

18:54.100 --> 18:55.299
Pop: Did he?
Mark: Yeah.

18:55.434 --> 18:56.834
Pop: I don't remember that.

18:56.903 --> 18:59.170
But my brain is frozen.

18:59.172 --> 19:00.638
Here.

19:00.640 --> 19:03.974
Oh, good.

19:04.010 --> 19:08.379
I'm so sorry your anniversary
got ruined, mom.

19:08.514 --> 19:11.248
You know, there's no better way
for me to spend it.

19:11.384 --> 19:13.417
Just me and my family.

19:13.419 --> 19:14.752
And ritche.

19:14.887 --> 19:16.587
Yes!

19:16.722 --> 19:17.888
[quietly]
oh, nice.

19:17.957 --> 19:20.758
It's nice to be included.

19:20.760 --> 19:22.994
Adult mark:<i> I had started</i>
<i> asking questions to stall,</i>

19:23.129 --> 19:27.598
<i> But now I was asking</i>
<i> questions to listen.</i>

19:27.634 --> 19:29.633
Mom, when did you two meet?

19:29.669 --> 19:34.104
Well, that was a long,
long time ago.

19:34.174 --> 19:37.408
I had just gotten
my first apartment.

19:37.477 --> 19:39.610
And so, the fella
who used to live there,

19:39.745 --> 19:43.681
He showed up at my door
and he wanted his mail.

19:43.683 --> 19:48.352
So we got to talking,
and I gave him his letters,

19:48.388 --> 19:50.888
And then he came back
the next week.

19:50.890 --> 19:54.058
And the week after that.

19:54.193 --> 19:56.928
Eventually he
asked me out to lunch.

19:57.063 --> 19:59.630
I kept mailing myself letters
so I'd have an excuse

19:59.632 --> 20:03.234
To talk to the gorgeous girl
in apartment 5.

20:03.369 --> 20:07.338
You never told me that!

20:07.473 --> 20:10.208
Mark: Well...
He's good at keeping secrets.

20:10.343 --> 20:13.211
I mean, after all,
he was basically a spy.

20:13.346 --> 20:15.846
Adult mark:<i> Telling secrets,</i>
<i> sharing stories--</i>

20:15.915 --> 20:17.915
<i> Connecting with</i>
<i> the people in your life</i>

20:17.917 --> 20:20.484
<i> Can make the dark times</i>
<i> seem brighter.</i>

20:20.553 --> 20:21.752
[all gasp]

20:21.887 --> 20:23.588
Mary: The power's back!
Pop: Hallelujah!

20:23.723 --> 20:25.256
Turn the bloody heat up!

20:25.258 --> 20:26.324
Mike jr: Hey!

20:26.459 --> 20:27.658
Mary: Oh, thank god!

20:27.793 --> 20:31.095
You're back in one piece,
my radio star!

20:31.097 --> 20:32.463
I didn't really
do all that much.

20:32.598 --> 20:34.465
I just let everyone else
do the talking.

20:34.467 --> 20:37.268
Ah, the most important part
of reporting isn't talking.

20:37.270 --> 20:39.403
It's listening.

20:39.538 --> 20:41.905
Oh, that reminds me: The news!

20:41.941 --> 20:43.874
Adult mark:<i> The best</i>
<i> movies I'd ever seen</i>

20:43.876 --> 20:46.877
<i> Lived in my family's memories.</i>

20:46.879 --> 20:51.082
<i> Who needed porky's when you</i>
<i>had stories about bob bartlett,</i>

20:51.084 --> 20:55.185
<i> Secret bases, and romance?</i>

20:55.255 --> 20:57.421
You know, there's a part
of me that almost wishes

20:57.556 --> 21:01.659
That the power
would go back out.

21:01.794 --> 21:04.428
Yeah, me too.

21:04.563 --> 21:06.430
Oh, sweet!
You guys got porky's!

21:06.565 --> 21:08.498
Mark: No, don't!
Ritche: No!

21:08.534 --> 21:11.635
Mike sr: Oh no, that's just
some old cartoon the kids got.

21:11.638 --> 21:15.973
[upbeat funk music playing]

21:16.108 --> 21:18.709
Good god, is that a boob?

21:23.116 --> 21:27.852
♪

21:27.987 --> 21:32.056
♪

21:32.125 --> 21:36.327
♪

21:36.462 --> 21:40.531
♪

21:40.600 --> 21:44.735
♪

21:44.804 --> 21:48.405
♪

21:48.474 --> 21:51.908
♪
